      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Ethanol is simply the latest in the long string of disastrous agribusiness strategies that squander the planet's biotic potential as surely as the pillage of fossil fuels threatens the very survival of mankind.</p>
        <p>A sustainable agrarian culture must return to the soil the nutrients, minerals and biomass needed to support the next year's crops. Ecosystems in the natural world are highly optimized to recycle the mass they generate. Otherwise, life would not persist.</p>
        <p>Larry Gilg  Austin, Tex., May 2, 2006</p>
      </block>
